text: Lyès Bouyacoub (born 3 April 1983) is an Algerian heavyweight judoka who won African Championships in 2014 and 2015, placing second in 2013 and 2016. He competed at the 2016 Olympics, but was eliminated in the third round. ==References== Category:1983 births Category:Living people Category:Algerian male judoka Category:Olympic judoka of Algeria Category:Judoka at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:African Games gold medalists for Algeria Category:African Games medalists in judo Category:Mediterranean Games bronze medalists for Algeria Category:Mediterranean Games medalists in judo Category:Competitors at the 2011 All-Africa Games Category:Competitors at the 2015 African Games Category:Competitors at the 2018 Mediterranean Games
